values:
[mood| amused] [music| the videos I'm watchin!] After seeing Hard Gay for the first time (not sure why I never actually watched anything by him ever, I've known about him for years) in this video that posted a little while back ... I randomly watched some more. I haven't laughed so hard in a very long time ^^ This clip especially had me in tears and not able to breath I was laughing so hard ... I'm not even entirely sure why I found it quite so funny, but it was great!
Online Videos by Veoh.com Why is he called Hard Gay Razor Ramon? Razor Ramon was a pro wrestler in the WWF or something over here years back~ (@_@;) Hoooooo! v(^o^)v EDIT: I have posted 5 times in the last 5 days (O___O) Holy crap! That is madness.

[mood| curious] [music| Horie Yui with UNSCANDAL - Scramble] Okay, so I really need to find a bunch of black lace. I haven't seen black lace around the few stores I have gone to, haven't made it to Queen St. yet to look, but thought some of you might know where was a good place to look for lace, and where it might not rape my wallet too badly. And as long as the weather holds and doesn't rain, I will be making a Queen St. fabric store run on Tuesday, so if anyone is interested in joining me, feel free o(^-^)o These are pics of the basic idea for the kinds of lace that I am looking for. I'm guessing that the side panels in the skirt are a fabric style lace, and not an actual spooled lace. Also, if anyone would mind giving me some pointers for making ruffley poofy loli style skirts I would be in much appreciation of tips! As far as I can guess you would just gather it all in on the elastic waste and then it does the ruffle/poof *has no idea what you call what happens on those skirts* on it's own? I know some of you do the loli thing, so I am guessing you know (o^-')b I was interested in doing an order with you, but any of the laces that I liked didn't come in black DX

[mood| pissed off] [music| alice nine. - FANTASY] Gah .. so my ride to the freaking dance it well over an hour late ... we are 1/2hr late for the dance already ... I am so angry!!!! I knew I should have just gone on the stupid public transit to get there ... *flails* Photo whoring makes me happier ... Vampire Shou <333 EDIT: They are on their way now ... about freaking time DX

[mood| irritated] [music| Gazette - Sugar Pain] Okay, so I bought a pair of violet contact lenses that I saw in a store while in Japan. They were a reasonable price, so I figured that even if I ended up not being able to put them in or some other bad thing that made it so I didn't wear them much, it wasn't a huge loss. Yay impulse buying! My parents are dead against me getting coloured contacts, and have been since I started wanting them in Grade 9. My Dad is away at work today so I figured I could handle one mad parent. So I finally tried to put them in today, or rather one ... as my right eye is getting a stye again I think ... so I didn't want to mess with it. So ya, after some initial trouble getting the contact actually on my eye, I got it on ... but I really doesn't fir my eye properly, the hole for my pupil is too big it seems, and has a gap at the bottom? haha anyway, kind of sad that they don't fit me properly ... but at least it wasn't a huge expense. I guess I need to get lenses properly fitted for me to wear them ... so that means it probably won't happen, because getting them from the Optomitrist is stupidly expensive. So hopefully I will wear the one violet eye to CNA on firday, and after that I'll see what happens. Anyway, here are a couple pics ... excuse my shoddy appearance, I couldn't be bothered to do my hair or anything just for a couple pics.

[mood| infuriated] [music| LOST AGE - Sign to Birth] Okay, before I attempt to start the job of writing about my trip I have to say one thing ... I am so freaking pissed off at my family right now. Yestarday all they did was give me a stupidly hard time about EVERYTHING DX What the hell. I won't go into it ... but seriously, WTF?!?! Way to make me even more depressed about having to come back to shity Canada to go back to shity school I hate and am going to have to fight and struggle through this year even more than last year. Way to make me feel better about everything, picking on me for anything and everything and nothing, I have no freaking idea what the hell was going on, I can see my Dad being like that ... but my Mom is never like that with me. I wanted to just scream at them, but my Grandma was out for supper (I really don't get along with her either, she still expects me to come and sleep over, hello I'm 22, not 10 x__x Seriosusly, WTF.) So I held my tongue and just took all the BS that was being thrown at me. I am still so freaking pissed off ... I can't remember when I have felt so betrayed and angry ... this was not what I needed right now ... both my parents were all "we miss you" which is wierd as hell to hear from my Dad, and then they treat me way worse than I have ever been treated in memory, ya, you guys really wanted me back and missed me. I am so doing everything in my power to freaking go back to Japan and do what I want, screw everything. Okay, now that I have that off my chest, onto my trip. I am going to start at the begining I guess since that makes sense. Even though it is torture to not just go on about the alice nine. live, hahaha, but good things come in time! lol So I surprised the hell out of myself and didn't get sick from my nerves at all the entire trip. I still can't believe it .. this is unheard of for me @__@ I am very thankful for not getting sick though ... perhaps I am finally getting over it. That would be nice. AUG 4th: The start of my trip! Stayed up the whole night before my flight doing last minute shit *cough*finishingalicenine.sgifts*cough* and finishing packing ... lol ... I procrastinate way too much. I was all good and dealing with things really well, got to the airport, got my boarding pass and checked my luggage, then I went to say bye to my parents and Mom was almost crying x_x Seriously, I'm gone to college longer than I would be gone on the trip. So ya, that rattled me a little, but I was still good. Got through all the airport stuff and then went to wait at my flight gate for an hour or so until I had to board my flight. I was good up until about 1/2 hour before my flight, at which point I started freaking out thinking "What the hell am I thinking going on this trip? I have never been on a plane in memeory ... etc" all kinds of negative stuff. By time I was on the plane I was almost hyperventalating and in tears. Hahaha, I bet the guy a seat over from me was like "WTF is wrong with this girl?" I freaked out even more when we started to take off. I DO NOT LIKE SPEEDING DOWN THE RUNWAY IN THE PLANE. It terrifies me, it feels like the plane is going to go out of control and crash, this bothered me everytime I had to take off in a plane on the trip. I didn't get any better until well after take off, I guess I finally accepted everything, and after that I was okay for everything else, but ya, rocky start, ahahaa. Got to Chicago where I had to change planes, and I was welcomed with a lovely 5hr delay on the flight to Beijing. JOY. Haha, anyway it wasn't too bad really, I listened to my ipod and got a Straberries and Creme Frappachino from Starbucks and just relaxed and dozed some. The flight to Beijing was long >__> close to 13hrs, and the food was blah, and there was only a little TV screen in the aisle at the front of the section of seats and then a big projector deal in the middle section of seats, so I could only see about 1/2 the screen or just moving colours on the little TV so that kind of sucked to try to watch the movies, but oh well it wasn't too bad. I had a window seat so I watched outside a lot. Looking down on the clouds is so cool, and going over the North Pole area was also very cool. I actually dealt with the long ass plane ride better than I thought I would. I figured I would have been an antsy nutcase about 4 hours into it. lol. Got to Beijing and through all the arrival stuff fine. I was a little worried and freaked out since I didn't have an address fro where I was staying, I was affraid I would run into trouble with that, but I didn't so I was very very relieved after that. Got my luggage and went out to the arrival area and I hear "REBECCA!!!!!" lol .. I have never been so happy to hear someone call my name XD lol ... So ya, Amy () scared some of the people around her, but we found each other right away so that was really really good for me. We took a taxi with her Dad back to where we would be staying. It was a little surprising to see some of the extreme poverty and living conditions in parts of Beijing, I wasn't really prepared for that at all. Anyway we dropped our stuff off, had a little something to eat at a place nearby and then retired for the night and planned to start the sightseeing the next morning at 8/9 area. END AUG 5th AUG 6th: The Forbidden City I slept pretty well that night, so I was all cocky about jetlag and having beaten it XD lol. I would find out later I was not above jetlag, hahaha. So the first thing we set out to see was the Forbidden City. (Be forewarned I look really stupid and out of it in almost all of the pics) The big one was squishing a little one!!! Hahaha, I thought it was cool XD So ya, that was the Forbidden City. It was pretty cool, very crazy details on everything. It was my first real taste of the HEAT as well. Since I had arrived in the evening the night before it wasn't too bad outside, but ya ... stupidly hot and humid out, even first thing in the morning. I was very very thankful for the airconditioned areas that had stuff to see in them. A/C is truly a huge blessing. After the Forbidden City we went out to KFC for lunch. Haha, it was so odd to be going to KFC in China, lol ... it seemed kind of wrong to me, lol. And then we went shopping! o(^-^)o I bought a really fun skirt that I love, but I needed girly shoes to wear with it, so maybe I can wear it here sometime, as I do have a pair of girly shoes here at home. And we also went to this anime store ... and stuff was so cheap!!! It was mind blowing! So ya, bought a fair bit of stuff there, haha. Went out for supper at this fancy Russian type restaurant. The food was pretty good. And I found out that I enjoy Borsh Soup XD Here is a pic of the ceiling of the place. And that is more or less what happened on the 6th. AUG 7th: Tackling The Great Wall of China So ya, jetlag bit me in the ass and I only slept a few hours. DX We headed out around 10 I think. It took a good hour or so to get out to the part of The Great Wall of China that we would be climbing, it was the part at Badling. I was really surprised at how mountainy the terrain became. I really knew nothing about China at all before I left, so ya, I wasn't expecting mountainish scenery. We looked through the Museum first before we went to climb, there were some pretty cool pictures and stuff. Then onto the climb. Amy's Dad decided he wasn't going to join us on the climb, so Amy and I headed out. All I can say is climbing The Great Wall of China was easily the most physically strenuous thing I have ever done. It was right over noonhour so it was hot as shit, thank god for the little bit of cool breeze that would blow every once in a while, it made it tolerable. So ya, most of the climb was between a 30-45 degree incline of ramps or stairs, and the stairs were all uneven, none of them were the same height, so you had to pay really close attention to what you were doing with your feet, and also all the grout was sticking out above the tiles everywhere, so it was really easy to catch your toe and trip ... It was a really hazardous experience o___O Anyway, after dying and sweating and such, we got to the highest point at this area of The Great Wall. Amy and I figured it would be easy clear sailing for the trip back down, but we were sorely mistaken. Going down such a steep incline when your legs are dead from climbing up is not a cool thing. My toes were slamming in the toes of my shoes with each step down and my legs were shaking and total jelly. I was so scared that my legs were just going to give out and I would fall and that would be the end because it was so steep if you fell you would just keep falling. Anyway roughly 3hrs after we headed out Amy and I successfully made it back down to safety and completed our climb of The Great Wall of China. Picture time! (next pic is totally horrible of me, but it shows off the view well, so here it is despite me looking crappy XD ) Amy and I after the climb. We climbed to the highest part you can see to the right of the picture. I decided to try to take some pan pics with my camera, this is how it turned out. After the climb we got drinks and headed out. I was feeling a little less than stellar, but nothing too bad, I figured once I got my drink into me I would feel fine again, but ya, I got feeling more and more nauseous as the car ride home progressed. I ended up actually being sick, thank god Amy's Dad had got me a book on the Great Wall and it was in a bag, so I threw the book out of the bag and proceded to be sick in the bag ~_~ lovely. But ya, sick in bag and not all over the car = good thing. So when we got home I passed out for a few hours. After I woke up and felt with it, we went out for dinner. We got Beijing Duck (I think that was what it was, Anyway a Beijing specialty) it was quite tastey and Kung Pow Chicken, I <3 Kung Pow Chicken! It was sooooooo yummy!!! Afterwards we walked around in the area, there were tons of little shops and also this strip of bars along this river type thing, it was really cool, they all had the bar/restaurant on one side of th street and then had tables and couches and stuff set up on the other side of the street beside the water. Very pretty. We decided to get dessert, and after sitting down at 3 different places, none of which actually had any kind of real desserts, just alcohol, we finally found a place that had all kinds of smoothies and such, haha, so we ate there. After that it was back home to sleep, and then shopping the next day. AUG 8th: Shopping I won't go into any details here, but to sum everything up: ~Everything being retardedly cheap and being able to bargin down prices is totally amazing. ~Almost all skrits and pants in Asian clothing WILL NOT FIT ME. I am just too big >__> damn hips and waist being like a solid 2" too big *cries* This would end up being the most traumatising realization for me. ~Shoes also generally wouldn't fit. DX ~So many people commented on how white I was XD lol. Thank you Amy for translating all the random comments for me, it was rather entertaining. This was one of the mall places we went to. I was greatly amused by the amimals on the roof o(^-^)o AUG 9th: More Shopping More of the same. Also we went to a meeting thing for the tour to Japan. It was rather amusing, they kept repeating to be on time, don't be late, over and over .. lol ... it was hillarious with Amy translating it to me. I got into the habit of taking pictures of all my drinks on the trip, lol. Here is the start of it. Seeing the Sprite in Chinese entertained me ^^ AUG 10th: Leaving for Japan!!! I think I have written enough to kill you guys already, so I will stop here for today. I will make Japan my next post. Depending on how it goes, I may need to break it up into more than one post. We will see how it goes. Overall Beijing was fun. It was really overcast and smoggy though, and not really somewhere I would go back to for a trip again I don't think, but I had a great time with Amy and her Dad, and I appreciate them both taking me around and treating me so amazingly for my whole stay there. Thanks so much Amy!!!

[mood| grateful and sad] [music| alice nine. discography] Well I am back home now. It is a very sad thing to have left Japan and be back to real life again. However, my time away was amazing, I truly had a wonderful time, and for that I am forever grateful. I still can hardly believe that the whole thing actually happened. The alice nine. live was easily the most amazing thing to ever happen in my life. I will do everything in my power to see them again as soon as possible. There are just no words to describe how incredibly happy and complete seeing them perform live made me. It was even better than I had imagined. Enjoy their hotness! <333 I can't wait for the release of their DVD Single NUMBER SIX., it will be awesome! I owe huge huge thanks to KiKi () for being such an amazing friend and helping me out so much. Without all your amazing help this trip and getting to see alice nine. live just wouldn't have happened. Thank you so much for helping to make my dreams come true. *giant hugs* Next time we will rock the alice nine. live from the front row and make all the fangirls stare at our cosplay hotness before the live! o(^-^)o Also a big thanks to Emelina () for taking me around Harajuku and letting me stay at your place. It was great to meet you, and I really really appreciate you helping me out! *hugs* And Amy () you also have huge thanks from me, as I also had a lot of help from you in getting to Japan. Staying with you in Beijing was awesome and you totally rock for acting as translator for me for almost 2 weeks *hugs* I had a ton of fun hanging out with you while I was on the first 2 legs of my trip. Thank you so so much for everything!!! *hugs* I will be doing several updates covering the different parts of my trip as I would totally kill you all if I tried to put it all in one post, hahaha, so I will break it down into more managable chunks. I will hopefully get started on the first part tomorrow, I am too dead from jetlag and a little too sad about not being in Japan anymore to do much of anything today except sleep. I hope everyone on my f-list is doing well. There is no way I can go back through 3 weeks of entries so I apologize if I have missed something important at all. Time to sleep again. -_- zzZzZZ

[mood| nervous] [music| Gazette - The Murders TV] I am still in a state of disbelief that this trip is actually happening ... my flight is in about 12 hrs and I am just kind of numb to the fact it seems ... I would have thought that I would be a complete basket-case by know totally freaking out ... but I am in this strange calm state where I am just really mellow. I am sure I will freak out once I actually get to the airport and am on my own, it will really sink in what I am doing then. Hahaha. It sucks, I have a kind of ingrown toenail on my left big toe, and I had been soaking it for a couple weeks and it was seeming to get kind of better, then all of the sudden on Monday it was way way worse, so painful and all swollen and icky .. so went to the Emergency room at the hospital and had the Doctor look at it ... he cut off a chunk of my toenail and dug around a bit (hurt like a SOB) and then said it should be fine O__O I expected to get some antibiotics or something because it was infected ... but ya .. nothing ... and the first day it seemed better, but the last 2 it has only been sort of okay ... so I really hope it stays okay for my whole trip, having a messed up toe will be complete suckage. STORM: There was a wild ass storm here last night. My Mom and I were driving back to the house and on the left it was a normal sunset type sky and on the right it was this pitch black cloud that went forever ... it was scary .. the side under the black cloud looked really messed up ... I wish I had my camera to try and do a panoramic shot .. it was so bizarre. Anyway, we just get in the driveway when all hell breaks loose, the wind picked up and the rain started pelting down and lightening was ripping through the sky, I jumped out of the car to go start getting the horses in. We got everone in and got everything all closed up, and just as I went to run back up to the house it started raining so hard that it actually hurt a lot getting hit by the rain, and it was raining so hard I couldn't see infront of me at all, it was crazy. When I finally got into the house I was so soaked it was like I had jumped into a pool and just climbed out, I was that soaked .. it was wild, I've never been in rain like that before. There has been some wicked rain, but this was something I had never experienced before. Also!!! I keep meaning to mention something here and I never do~! Hahaha. I am so totally addicted to the show "So You Think You Can Dance" It is so freaking good!!! Dancing is hands down one of the coolest things ever, all the different styles are so amazing, what an incredible artform. And ... I LOVE TRAVIS! *is a Travis fangirl* He has cool hair and has an awesome personality and is a wicked dancer. I have been watching the show for the past month or 2 and next week is the season finale and I am going to miss it *cries* I told my Mom she has to tape it for me. The 3 guys left are all awesome, I will be so upset to see any of them kicked off, I have to watch tonight to see which guy and girl are kicked off *is scared for Travis* Hahaha .. they are doing a tour where the top 10 dancers perform, I so want to go the the show that is in Buffalo, NY. Mom and I are seriously thinking of trying to get tickets to go. I will scream for Travis XD He's only 18, but he is damn hot!!! Here is a bunch of pics from the show's website that I threw together So I will be away from LJ until I get back on the 23rd ... and then there will be much catching up to do I am sure XD hahaha. I'll miss you all! *hugs*

[mood| anxious & excited] [music| OLIVIA inspi REIRA - a little pain] Well it looks like everything is in order for my trip now *so relieved* I got my Passport and Chinese Visa without a problem, have my flight tickets, and have a bunch of money exchanged into Japanese Yen and USD Travellers Cheques, as well as a little bit of money for my stay in China ... whatever you call that currency, short for is RMB or something *shrugs* So ya, only have to pick up a few little things and throw it all in my suitcase and I am good to go I think, hahah. I am starting to get really freaked out now that my departure date is so close @__@ I have window seats for my whole trip over to Beijing so that made me really happy ^_^ and apparently you get assigned your seat when you check in for the flight leaving Osaka, so hopefully I can get a window seat for that flight as well. Have an aisle seat for the trip from Chicago to Toronto, but it is a less than 2hr flight so that won't be too bad. I am so excited for this ... I feel like it is something I really had to do at this point in my life. And hopefully with this trip I will be able to make my way through this final year of animation and then I am so done school!!! I am still really wanting to try to do the teaching english in Japan thing when I finish school, but I will have to look into what kind of money you make as I will have a fairly large debt to pay back to the Ontario Government when I finish, so I will need to be able to make enough money to survive and have fun in Japan for the year as well as pay off my student loan. Went over to Steph's () for an anime night get together on the 22nd, but I was the only person who showed up .. haha so instead of watching anime she brought me to the dark side of JDRAMAS!!! .. lol ... she got me hooked on Nobuta wo Produce, we watched the first 7 eps and then were too tired to read any more subtitles hahaha. I just finished watching the last 3 eps last night ^__^ It was such a good series! I will have to check out a few more dramas when I get back from my trip. Anyone have any suggestions? Feel free to ignore this part. Emo Rant: I seem to have gotten into the horrible feeling of hopelessness and am just not trying to do anything it seems. There was so much shit I was supposed to be doing for the past few weeks once I had my flights booked for my flight, like doing my freaking Japanese audio lessons everyday so I would have a bit more knowledge of some basics ... but I felt like if I committed to preparing for the trip something would fall through for it again (like the passport or visa) LAME! I hate how I react to things, I am so negative about achieving anything, I always think I won't be able to do it, or what I do won't be good enough. Such a deconstructive thought process. I keep wishing that I could change it and get out of feeling this way, but the feeling gets in the way always. I am pondering if perhaps hypnosis would be able to help at all? If it can help people to quit smoking and such, maybe it would help. I hate being such a weak person, and because of my weakness it seems I am unable to change it. I am racking my brain trying to come up with gift ideas for the alice nine. members that I will give them at the live I go to, but I am having so much trouble coming up with ideas. Especially for Saga and Nao as those are the two members that I 'know' the least. Blah. My new hair o(^-^)o Hair Rant: I was really really sad about how the actual hair cut turned out. I told the hairdresser to leave most of the length for the side parts of my bangs/fringe and to keep the length at the back bottom (YAY jrock mulletness XD hahaha) But she cut off like everything DX it is all so short now ... there goes 6 months of trying to get my hair a certain way. Screw you hair chick .. I was so expecting it to be awesome, because the last time I went before AN to get it cut and coloured for my Shou cosplay she did an amazing job ... so I took back the ref pics I took the last time and said do this exactly again, except longer here and here ... I really don't get how hairdressers seem to never get hair right .. so stupid. But I guess it is kind of a blessing in disguise as I will be very glad to have short short hair when I hit the insane heat of East Asia on my trip in the following weeks. So as revenge to the shortness I bleached some parts XD lol. I had to cheer myself up, and no better way than making fun chunky colours!! I had so missed having mulit coloured hair .. it has been almost 10 years since my hair was one colour ... what a painful experience XD ahahahah. Blonde partial return of the Ruki stripe and then a chunk over my ear and back a little way across the back of my head. It turned out really fun, I had to get my Mom to help me and she has never done hair before, so she was really funny and cute doing it, and kept saying "It's not my fault if this turns out bad, you're the one who got me to do it." lol It all turned out well so it's all good. Also on a side note ... screw you eyebrows!!! I really really want to do jrock eyebrows ... so badly ... but it is really scary to think about actually doing it ... it would be such high maintenance as my eyebrows really aren't the type that would go along with this easily *curses her eyebrows* And then if I did want to grow them out again, it would look so bad for so long >_< But Shou-like eyebrows are so hot!!!! *struggles with the idea* Horses: Training is going really really well with my darling Cileos. I love riding her so much!! We get along so very well. But it is stupid for me to expect my Mom to keep her for me when I will be gone to school for 8 months and then possibly gone to Japan for a year after that. It isn't fair to Cileos or my family to expect that. So serious attempts will be made to sell her, I will cry, but it is for the best, I know this. I will make my best attempts to have her trained well so she will be able to be sold to a good loving home who will show her and she will be able to accomplish many great things with her talent!!! And then her mama can be oh so proud of her Killy-baby doing great things *nods* Also Happy Birthday Nao!!! Even though his b-day is long over in Japan and almost done here .. but yes ... Happy Brithday none the less!!!! lol, I so fail ... it took me over 3 days to finally get through writing this post .. haha I am so not in the lj mood at all lately.

[mood| jubilant & excited] [music| alice nine. - CORONA] Okay, so now that I have paid for the flights, I figure it is safe to say I am infact going to Japan in a few weeks XD *freaks out* I am leaving from Toronto on August 4th at 10:00am and will be back on the 23rd at 9:06pm. I am first going to Beijing to meet up with Amy () and chill there for a few days, do some cheap ass shopping and have general good times ^__^ Then her, her cousin (who conveniently is pretty much fluent in Japanese) and I are going on a tour of Japan, it's 6 days, the 8th to the 14th of August. Stops on tour: Day 1: Beijing to Osaka Day 2: Osaka to Kobe Day 3: Kobe back to Osaka and then to Kyoto Day 4: Kyoto to Nagoya to Yokohama to Tokyo (where we will be praying for non-early shop closing so we can wander at night) Day 5: Tokyo (For the love of god I want to bring my Shou cosplay and just stay at Harajuku all day T__T but I don't think that is going to happen. Damn you tour for not starting a day earlier so free time day was today so I could do what I want! I would probably die of heat wearing Shou anyway, and it would take up precious space in my planned minimal luggage) Day 6: Tokyo (more wandering) and then the tour goes back to Beijing at the end of the day. I am then going off into the wilderness of Japan on my own XD haha, well hopefully not on my own, as I hope to have met up with at some point durring the afternoon before Amy and her cousin have to leave to go back to the airport. Hopefully will do an evening of hanging out with and then stay the night either at a hotel near where she lives or possibly with her if her roomies and house owners don't mind me crashing there. Then we have the morning of the 15th to do some shopping and hanging outness and then around noon-2 area I hope to get on the Shinkansen and head down to Fukuoka to meet up with KiKi () who I will be bumming in with for the remainder of my stay in Japan!! GOING TO SEE ALICE NINE. ON THE 20TH!!!! OMG!!! KiKi is to be worshipped for successfully getting us tickets <333 You are the best!!! *loves you* Have the 21st to maybe do some shopping in Fukuoka? But will likely be dead from the live x_x Anyway then heading out of Osaka back to Toronto on the 23rd at 5:55pm so I will have to head out from KiKi's first thing in the morning to get to the airport a little after noonish *nods* So that is the wild and crazy adventure that I am now going on!!! All I have to do now is hope to hell my Passport and Chinese Travel Visa get approved. That would suck so hugely if something happened there x_x it would be beyond words. So points for people involved with my adventure: : I won't be coming back to Beijing anymore .. as the flights worked out to infact be cheaper for me to just do 2 oneway flights. I so love the travel agent I used she totally got me great prices! (well great considering how late I was booking, and compared to all the over travel agaents I had looking for me) : Anything you see that won't work for you or would work better if I did something else please let me know so I can try to arrange otherwise. I will hopefully be with you from the evening of the 15th until the morning of the 23rd *hugs* I am so excited to see you! We can keep emailing back and forth too to figure stuff out *get excited whenever she sees a notification of an email from you XD* : Um, I guess we need to decide when and where we are going to meet on the 14th. I will be in Harajuku for sure, as my friend I am on the tour with really wants to shop like mad there. Also whatever is happening with me staying somewhere ... if I'm not staying with you than any help you can give me with getting a hotel near you would be awesome! And we talked about getting me to the Shinkansen on the 15th already earlier. *hugs* I hope to get to meet up with you <3 ANYONE ELSE who has any advice for the insanely long flights or travel in general or things about Japan, the cities we are touring etc. PLEASE SHARE!!! <333 I want to know as much I can from everyone's experiences and knowledge! Thank you! Okay ... that is all the Japan related stuff I guess o(^-^)o *dances around* I'll do a brief rundown of the past week and a bit since I pretty much dissappeared off LJ since my last post on Shou's b-day. Sat. 8th ~ Beach/Karoke/KBBQ: Went on a day of fun and adventure in Toronto with Steph (), Hahn (), Kevin () and some other random people Steph and Hahn knew. We went to have a picnic on the beach, which was so acuratly summed up by Steph in her lj ... Despite the sand BURNING LIKE HELL, the rocks HURTING LIKE HELL and the water COLD LIKE HELL FROZEN OVER, it was SUPA. Was much fun, I got some sunburn on my back >__> which was sucktastic ... but it wasn't super bad like Steph's or one of the guys who came. Very glad I put on lots of sunscreen, but I guess I missed the middle of my back XD We then went to Karaoke, it was my first time ever going and it was pretty fun, I battled with my hate for my voice and total suckage at singing and I sang some songs XD I must admit it was pretty fun, hahah. After 3hrs of Karaoke fun we headed down to Korean BBQ, and I was feeling less than stellar, hardly any sleep due to my messed up sleeping from work scheduel and lots of sun = somewhat nauseous Rebs. So I wasn't going to do all you can eat ... but nothing else on the menu was much less expensive ... and after getting some much needed water into me I felt a little better, so went with all you can eat XD Didn't eat as much as I usually could, but didn't want to risk making myself feel ill like I did last time from over eatting ... hahah. We then headed back to sleepover at Steph's I pretty much passed out as soon as we got there ... I was exhausted, woke up every little while as everyone else was playing Mahjong then Monopoly for several hours XD haha. Sun. 9th ~ Pacific Mall: My first time ever going to the place. It was pretty cool ... lots and lots to look at! Got to see several people I haven't seen for a long while, except for a few minutes at AN or at the last KBBQ, but I didn't get to talk much there, just ate and then ran off to work. I was so very happy to get to spend time with you guys!! Chris I missed you, so it was so nice to see you for a solid amount of time! After much wandering around P-Mall and a short trip to Kikiwai with a couple people we all went out to dinner at Jack Astors. It was a lot of fun, I guess I haven't been there since my first year of college in 2002, went several times then ... it was good, but I was really really sad that their amazing garlic bread doesn't come unlimited with their meals now T__T So I had to pay for one, but oh god, it was worth every penny, SO YUMMY! I love good garlic bread *is very fussy, loves lots and lots of garlicness* After an entertaining dinner everyone was parting ways .. and I was like "OH SHIT NEVER CALLED HOME!" I figured I would be heading home around 5-6 area ... and it was then 8:30. So I called home, was in shit for not calling as parents had no idea where I was or how to get into contact with me (my cell was pretty much dead after having it one for a lot of the day before, which was surprising, usually it lasts a couple days being left on) So ya, mom was freaking out that I was kidnapped raped and murdered by this point >___> So I ended up going home with Steph to get picked up by Dad there. Steph and I had some good chatting while it was just the 2 of us ... too bad my Dad showed up a when he did, I would have liked to keep talking. Oh well, next time!!! Ended up I wasn't in too much shit ... parents were just worried because I am usually really good about checking in and such. So ya, fun day! And look what I randomly found while in P-Mall!!! XDD Hahah .. I had to keep trying to explain to everyone what Daikon~sama's significance was .. lol, it was funny. The store had a bunch of bigger sized ones too, but this keychain one was just way too cute! I had to buy it X3 While I was gone for the whole weekend I was going insane wondering if KiKi had been successful in getting our alice nine. tickets, as the went on sale at 10am on the 8th. Woke up Monday morning and checked her LJ and the awesome news was there <3 tickets for us!! YAY! So ever since then I have been going insane trying to figure everything out with Amy and KiKi and finding out about flights, passport, visa and everything. All I can say is thank god it is mostly over, I don't think I have ever had such a stressful time of things ... x_x Today: Yestarday I called all the travel agencies in town to look for flights for me, and in the end American Express Travel totally rocked everyone else big time! The lady who helped me was awesome and got me great flights with pretty damn good prices (hell of a lot cheaper than all the other places and cheaper than anything I had found online to) So today, I had to go into town to get my passport shit signed by my guarantor and then went to the travel agency to get final plans made for flights and pay. It felt so amazing to buy the airplane tickets today, and to tell Amy to book me in on the Japan tour thing <333 Right after getting the tickets bought, my Dad drove me to the Passport office in Whitby (about a 45min drive) and we get there only to realize I hadn't brought my Birth Certificate DX He was so mad at me .. but it wasn't totally my fault, he hardly let me run to the bathroom when we got home after booking the flights, so I didn't have a chance to check over the forms and such. And I NEVER am in charge of filling out forms and such, my Dad always does all my paperwork shit ... so I was so stressed filling it out and making sure everything was right that I didn't even think to check the checklist thing they give you to make sure you have everything you need. So we drove home in total silence .. it sucked, no radio no talking, nothing, just angry vibes from him directed at me ... We get home and he starts bitching to my Mom about how stupid I was to not bring it, there is a freaking checklist that lists all the shit you need. Ya thanks, I'm right here ... anyway Mom defended me some saying that I have done pretty good to do all I have done by myself because I have never had to try to deal with anything like this ever ... so ya ... got my Birth Certificate, checked the checklist thing to make sure I had everything now, grabbed my ipod so I could have music on the trip this time, and headed back over. Everything went smoothly, should get my passport in 2wks, then I have to run into Toronto to the Consulate General of the P. R. China in Toronto as soon as I get my passport and pay extra fees to get my visa proccessed in a day so I will have it in time to leave on the 4th @__@ Holy crap passports and shit cost a lot, man ... it's brutal. I am a little excited, but I think I am wary of getting excited about this whole thing as it has kept falling through for the past 4 months ... but I finally have success!!! ... I hope. *crosses finger that everything else goes fine* Horse Talk: Also this week I rode for the first couple times in around 8 months, it was a great feeling <3 Also my darling girl Killer, haha I nicknamed her that as a baby when we bought her because female horses her colour have a reputation for being highstrung and tempermental, she is a little bit of these, but is a real mushy sweetheart. Her real name is Cileos ^_^ We started her back into training, so I was up on her back getting lead around by Mom after only one lesson, and she hadn't had anything done with her since we did some really basic starting to her riding 2 years ago ... I am so proud of her, she was such a star for remembering everything so wonderfully and accepting me back onto her back without question. I am going to cry when she is sold, but I can't keep more than one horse for myself, as I am hardly ever around to actually do anything with them, and they are stupidly expensive to keep. So I am going to fall even more in love with her doing her training and building a stronger bond .. and then have to sell her and never see her again. I will be the most devistated I have ever been about one of my babies leaving, Killer know she is my sweetheart, and is such a funny sweet girl with me. And she has the most amazing expressions with her eyes ... she has such immense character ... *is tearing up thinking about seeing her go within the next 6 months* Here is a pic of of my Killy~baby, it isn't very flattering, but you can see her. And finally, a pic of my barn kitty, because she is so prettiful! Her name is Marble, and she is 13, and drools in happiness when you sit down with her and pet her XD Kind of gross, but always makes me laugh, it's so odd .. but she has done it basically ever since she was a kitten when we saved her from the Humane Society. She is an awesome kitty <333 Fear my posts when I have been gone for over a week!!
